And in the moſt happie Reygne of our late dread Sovereygne, king IAMES, of ever-bleſſed memorie,Iam. 6. parliam. 6. c. 70
                   it is ſtatuted in Parliament, That no handie-labour nor working bee vpon the LORD'S Day, nor anie wilfull remayning from divine Worſhip thereon. In both which our Salmond-Fiſhers notoriouſlie tranſgreſſe: and ſo are rebellious both to Divine and Humane Authoritie;


and to the Lawes both Ancient and Moderne; of Church, and Commonwealth.
